            <div type="translation">
            <p>Hegeso daughter of Proxenios.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Transcription from photo. The modern plaster cast is a replica of IG I, 3rd ed., 1289, an Attic grave stele dated to the last decade of the fifth century BCE.  Within the naisokos are depicted in releif a seated woman (presumably Hegeso) wearing a chiton and himation with her feet resting on a stool. In her left hand she reaches toward a pyxis held out to her by a maidservant dressed in a tunic and headdress standing before her.</p></div>
            

